Still going strong since it was established in 1997, business support services provider A2C Distributors has grown its range progressively. The company supplies a variety of tools and solutions to suit a customers’ needs and requirements. Of these, the company’s range includes furnace fuel, furnace and oven builders and the installation thereof, as well as bearings refurbishment, oil separators, as well as lifting equipment. Products available at this year’s Electra Mining Africa exhibition, in September, will include bearings, oil separators, magnetic probes, the Kenna metal inserts, as well as reflectors and pumps. In addition to this, A2C also has in-house engineering capabilities, and can supply tungsten carbide wear parts, temperature compensating micrometres, Adaptek pumps and more – all supplied and delivered at competitive prices. A2C Distributors has a Level 2 broad-based black economic empowerment rating, is tax compliant, has a central supplier database, or CSD, certificate, as well as material safety data sheet, or MSDS, in place.